msgid "Minimal Measures"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:4
msgid ""
"***As a general rule, we encourage conference organizers to implement all"
" the üçé measures and at least one of the ‚úÖ suggestions.***"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:6
msgid ""
"Making your conference inclusive and encouraging diversity is achievable."
" The measures below are explained in more depth in the other pages of "
"this Cookbook."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:8
msgid "What are the easiest and most impactful measures?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:10
msgid ""
"Just follow the measures below. They are explained in more depth in the "
"other pages of this Cookbook. Measures that are **easy to implement** and"
" have a **strong positive impact** are &quot;low-hanging fruit&quot; and "
"marked with a red apple emoji: üçé. Measures that take more effort but have"
" considerable impact are marked with a green checkmark: ‚úÖ."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:13
msgid "[Organizing Committee](03_organizing_committee.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:14
msgid ""
"‚úÖ The organizing committee itself should reflect the diversity you want "
"to create in your conference! Prioritizing diversity starts with you."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:17
msgid ""
"Conference chairs and lead organizers should take special care to recruit"
" an organizing committee that reflects the diversity of the event you "
"aspire to create."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:19
msgid "[Venue Selection &amp; On-Site Services](04_venue_selection.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:21
msgid "Accessibility Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:23
msgid "Consider attendees who may need accommodations for a disability"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:26
msgid "Mobility"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:28
msgid ""
"üçé Reserve seats in rooms for folks who might need it (wheelchair, "
"crutches, cane, etc.). Choose easily accessible seats, such as at the end"
" of a row on the aisle."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:30
msgid ""
"üçé Create wide aisles between chairs to make it easier for people who are "
"mobility-impaired to navigate the room."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:33
msgid "Disability"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:35
msgid ""
"üçé Provide large-text signs and easy-to-read maps. Ask conference "
"organizers to announce important information over the microphone, which "
"helps people with impaired vision."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:37
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Book sign-language interpreters and/or real-time captioning (someone "
"typing captions) for deaf and hard-of-hearing attendees.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:40
msgid "Bathrooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:42
msgid "Gender-Neutral Bathrooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:44
msgid ""
"üçé Post signs in the restroom and/or on the door instructing what to do if"
" you think someone is in the \"wrong\" restroom"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:47
msgid ""
"\"If you think someone's gender doesn't match the sign on the door, "
"please follow these steps: Don't worry about it, they know better than "
"you.\" (via [@LGBTplusBristol](https://twitter.com/lgbtplusbristol))"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:49
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Ensuring your conference has easily accessible gender-neutral restrooms"
" is a simple way to help non-binary and trans individuals feel included "
"and welcome at your conference.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:52
msgid "Toiletries/Supplies"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:54
msgid ""
"üçé Provide tampons and pads in all restrooms (some people who identify as "
"male have periods and may need them)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:57
msgid "üçé Dedicated rooms"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:59
msgid ""
"The rooms should be clearly labeled to prevent accidental entry, and "
"their locations should be provided in both the print and the online "
"conference directory and maps."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:61
msgid "Don't allow anyone (even organizers) to use the room for other purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:64
msgid "üçé Nursing & Pumping Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:66
msgid "Ensure there is a dedicated, single-occupancy space with lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:68
msgid "For the room to be optimally useful, these things are desired:"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:70
msgid ""
"Locking door, Comfortable chair, a desk or table next to the chair (to "
"set the pump, bottles, etc. on), no more than 4 feet from the nearest "
"electrical outlet, cleaning wipes, paper towels, and a garbage can, "
"masking tape and a marker for labeling milk bottles and pump parts, "
"proximity to a sink for hand washing and washing of pump parts, a "
"refrigerator for storage of pumped milk  in the pumping room or nearby, "
"dim lighting"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:72
msgid "üçé Gender-Neutral Bottle Feeding Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:74
msgid ""
"Bottle-fed babies can be fed by caregivers of any gender and also benefit"
" from a quiet, low-distraction, private space for feeding."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:76
msgid ""
"This should be a separate, additional room (NOT the same as the nursing "
"and pumping room) which should be clearly labeled. It could accommodate "
"multiple babies at a time and be equipped with multiple comfortable "
"chairs with broad armrests to facilitate bottle feeding positions, a "
"bottle warmer, paper towels, cleaning wipes and garbage can for "
"cleanliness, dim lighting and in a quiet area of the conference "
"center/venue"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:79
msgid "üçé Quiet Room"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:81
msgid ""
"A dedicated room for people who need a break from the stimulation of "
"being surrounded by people at the conference; no phone calls, "
"talking/socializing, notification beeps! People whose religions require "
"frequent prayer can make use of the quiet room."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:83
msgid "Consider \"quiet areas\" if a separate room is not possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:85
msgid "[Catering](05_catering.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:87
msgid ""
"Making sure that your attendees have something they can eat at mealtimes "
"is an important element of building an inclusive and welcoming "
"conference."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:89
msgid ""
"Best to have a sign/small label in front of each dish with a list of "
"ingredients and common labels (e.g. \"gluten-free, vegan, includes "
"peanuts\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:92
msgid "üçé Ask your caterer to create and provide the labels."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:95
msgid ""
"üçé Make sure to include a variety of beverages, in particular non-"
"alcoholic and non-caffeinated."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:96
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Common dietary needs to plan for gluten-free, dairy-free, vegan, "
"vegetarian, pork-free, shellfish-free, soy-free, kosher, halal, nut-free."
" Shellfish and peanut  especially are usually a serious allergy so take "
"extra care."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:98
msgid "[Code of Conduct (CoC)](07_code_of_conduct.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:100
msgid "Awareness"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:102
msgid ""
"Make sure that everyone involved in your conference/event is aware that "
"the CoC applies to them: that not only includes participants, but also "
"speakers, sponsors, committee members etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:104
msgid "üçé Tick box at registration that confirms that the participant has read it"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:106
msgid "üçé Include a copy of the CoC in the sponsor packet"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:108
msgid "üçé Mention that the CoC applies to the speakers in the speaker guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:110
msgid "üçé Ensure that CoC is easily accessible on the conference website"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:112
msgid "üçé Include a short version on the printed schedule as a reminder"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:114
msgid ""
"üçé Mention it in the welcome talk and at the start of every day, including"
" whom to contact if there is a problem/violation"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:117
msgid "[Participant and Speaker Selection](09_participant_selection.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:119
msgid "Speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:121
msgid ""
"üçé Consider the specific wording of how you solicit talks, e.g. call for "
"\"Speakers who have advice or expertise to share\" rather than \"experts "
"in best practices\""
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:123
msgid "Invited Speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:124
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Reach beyond the conference organizers' own networks. Take steps to go "
"out and find people who might be lesser-known but would make great "
"speakers. Look for more than just \"the usual suspects\" and reach out to"
" your wider network for ideas, suggestions, and introductions."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:126
msgid "Selecting Speakers"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:128
msgid "üçé Call For Proposals instructions -- be clear who you want"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:130
msgid ""
"In the solicitation, be transparent that you want a broad & diverse group"
" to share their expertise."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:132
msgid ""
"Let applicants know what criteria will be used to assess their submission"
" and how speakers will be chosen."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:135
msgid ""
"If your conference has a long history, and you're trying to change what "
"the program make-up, be up front about the kinds of people you want to "
"have speak, why, and how this may look different from years past."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:138
msgid "Call for Proposals Review"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:140
msgid ""
"‚úÖ There are many approaches to reviewing and selecting conference "
"contributions, and there is no foolproof type of review that always "
"avoids biases. Regardless of which approach you choose, open or "
"anonymized, we encourage you to make it \"double\" so that both parties "
"know each other (double-open) or neither party knows the other (double-"
"closed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:144
msgid "Attracting Attendees"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:146
msgid ""
"üçé Pay attention to the photos you use to advertise your event‚Äîwhat do "
"people look like who attend?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:149
msgid "[Event Registration](10_event_registration.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:150
msgid "What to ask on your registration form (and what not to ask)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:152
msgid "Preparing to meet accessibility needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:154
msgid ""
"üçé Ask registrants if they have any additional accessibility needs, and if"
" so, provide instructions on how to make the request."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:157
msgid ""
"\"Do you need any special accommodations to help make your time at the "
"conference comfortable and productive? (e.g. accessibility "
"considerations). Please [email](mailto:contact@myconference.com) and "
"include the details of your request.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:159
msgid "Demographic Info"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:161
msgid ""
"‚úÖ If you do collect demographic info, be thoughtful about the structure "
"of the questions so that they are inclusive and don't contribute to "
"alienating or \"othering\" marginalized people."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:164
msgid ""
"Not having an answer choice that matches your identity can be a very "
"alienating experience."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:167
msgid ""
"‚úÖ Take anonymity and data security seriously. Have a plan for limiting "
"access to this information and keeping it secure."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:169
msgid "Dietary Restrictions"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:171
msgid ""
"üçé Ask for dietary restrictions on the registration form. Some people have"
" severe allergies or dietary restrictions that can affect their ability "
"to attend the conference."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:173
msgid "Photo Policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:175
msgid ""
"üçé If you will have a photographer at your event, include information for "
"attendees explaining that they may be photographed and how to opt out in "
"the registration form."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:178
msgid ""
"(see lanyard/photography explanation under [Inclusive "
"Practices](11_inclusive_practices_during_checkin.md))"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:180
msgid "Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:182
msgid ""
"üçé Show the text of the Code of Conduct and a required check-box that the "
"registrant has read it and agrees to abide by it."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:184
msgid "[Childcare](06_childcare.md)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:186
msgid "‚úÖ Offer financial support for childcare."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:188
msgid "Build it into your budget."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:190
msgid ""
"Link it to sponsorships, or university partners, or make part of the "
"registration fee from all attendees go towards providing childcare "
"support as a service."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:191
msgid ""
"Add an option to the registration, e.g.: \"Donate $20 to help with "
"childcare costs.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:192
msgid ""
"Collect the data on the registration form. How many people would make use"
" of childcare services or grants?"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/02_minimal_measures.md:194
msgid ""
"In general, the two major options are either to 1) award childcare grants"
" (people decide how to spend it, e.g. on their home babysitter) or 2) "
"provide on-site services."
msgstr ""

